caption: The hike up and around this lighthouse can be quite steep and challenging. Just take your time, as the views are absolutely breathtaking! 😍 (📷: @johnedwardjames 📍: Neist Point, Scotland)

Almost 2,000 years ago, the Colosseum ran by the motto "Bread and Circuses" and allowed 50,000 people to enjoy spectacles and entertainment. We still think the Colosseum looks pretty spectacular today! (🎥: @oliverhl 📍: Rome, #Italy)
Norway🇳🇴 is this real! Imagine traveling the 8 kilometers of "Atlantic Ocean Road" as part of your daily commute. (📷: @twintheworld 📍: Atlantic Ocean Road, Norway)
Starting off the morning with a swing over the jungle 🌴Warning ⚠️: Not for those afraid of heights! (📷: @emmett_sparling 📍: #Bali)
Perfect day: 1) Walk around the sandstone cliffs 2)Take photos 3) Come back to the castle 4) Relax at the spa ✅ (📷: @vetrana 📍: Hrubá Skála, Czech Republic)
Great view of 'falls in the fall. Here's to @micanthonyhay for capturing the perfect autumnal scene. (🎥: @micanthonyhay 📍:Taughannock Falls, New York)

What a surprising pairing: a small Norwegian fishing village🎣 and a famous football stadium⚽️. Add in some modern art galleries, and bam, you have added another place to your Norway itinerary. (📷: @thomaseckhoff 📍: Henningsvær, Norway)

@stevint exclaims, "Thank goodness for all the bends, cause with the never ending views it gives tons of opportunities to stop." This pic gives us major fall fever! 🍁(📷: @stevint 📍:Cape Breton Island, Nova Scotia)

Overlooking the majestic Mongolian mountains. There are four mountain ranges in Mongolia- the Altai Mountains, the Gobi-Altai Mountains, the Khentii Mountains, and the Khangai mountains. Have you visited any? (📷: @jordhammond 📍: #Mongolia)
🔊sound on to hear the church bells in the distance. A sunrise look at the popular Lake Bled, Slovenia. (🎥: @ananya.ray 📍: Lake Bled)

@bradgeddesphotography says that exploring the streets in Chefchaouene "reminds me of watching The Smurfs when I was a kid" and honestly we agree 😂 Do you know why the walls are blue? Leave us a comment below! (📸: @bradgeddesphotography 📍: Morocco)
Magical mornings spent at Lake Louise in Canada. Swipe ⬅️ to see the full 🌈 (📷: @cumacevikphoto 📍: Lake Louise, Alberta)

Strolling down the streets of Luxembourg 🍁🍂 Thinking about a trip to the capital city? We recommend taking the tram around the city. With a complete audio guide and a hop on, hop off system, it is a a great way to learn the history of the city. (📷: @butnomatter.theroadislife 📍: Luxembourg, Luxembourg)

Perfect lake day conditions 🛶Ride a cable car up to Ebenalp and hike down to Seealpsee Lake in Switzerland. If you have time, visit Gasthaus Aescher- a restaurant built within the cliff for amazing views and Swiss fare! (📷: @everchanginghorizon & @jess.wandering 📍: Seealpsee Lake, #Switzerland)

@brahmino describes, "Awakened by the church bells, I took the opportunity to go to the terrace to see the Sun and capture the warm color of dawn. #🇬🇷" Mamma mia, what a dream morning😍🔔(🎥: @brahmino 📍: Andros, Greece)

Walking into the Arashiyama Bamboo Grove feels like you are in another world 😍#TravelTip: Visit the grove on a windy day to see how mesmerizing the bamboo stalks look as they sway back and forth. (📷: @danielkordan📍: Arashiyama Bamboo Grove, #Kyoto, Japan)

This area of Turkey is most known for its agriculture, winter sports and stunning nature🌱⛰. Salt mining used to be huge here, and this tradition still continues today! Where do you think the birds are flying to next?! 🐦 (🎥: @ahmet.erdem 📍: Çankırı, Turkey)

@chrisburkard reflects "....to see these complex glacial river systems with the naked eye gives you a whole new appreciation for their constantly changing beauty. No need to do anything fancy when they look this good straight off the phone. No edit, pure nature." 👀❄️(🎥: @chrisburkard 📍: Þjórsá, #Iceland)

Park your boat at Bled Island, then head right up to the church to pull the 'wishing bell.' Legend has it that pulling it will bring you good luck! Just remember- one wish per person!🍀🔔 (📷: @davide.anzimanni📍: Bled, Slovenia)

A man named Bruce lives in this super (aero)dynamic house! He is a member of the Aircraft Fleet Recycling Association (AFRA), which helps create new dwellings out of old planes ✈️. #SustainabilityTip: Transform old objects into new treasures! ♻️ (🎥: @uwo 📍: #Oregon, USA)
